bug.short_desc: brltty base package adds a dependency on python2
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
The dependency should be on python3 not python2 it brings in an entire stack that's not default.
The "python dependency is, unfortunately, correct, it's needed by the latex-access Contraction." should be split out into a sub package or it should use python3 because python3 is the default python stack in Fedora releases.
brltty-5.5-5.fc26 has been submitted as an update to Fedora 26. https://bodhi.fedoraproject.org/updates/FEDORA-2017-16b93b066d
Update is out for f26, but the build dies with a java segfault on ppc64le.
Adding Power64 tracking bug so the POWER team are aware of the issue
the segfault could be the recent IFUNC issue with glibc 2.26 vs gcc (https://lists.fedoraproject.org/archives/list/devel@lists.fedoraproject.org/message/UJDC6JZEXME2SWGEIAXAU6SE7RP5N3RH/)
